Ratchet Rockers chiming in here

During the offseason between the end of 2021 season and now we have taken our first stab at using the Command based programming offered in WPILib. We took our 2020 robot and started from scratch and added a few of the subsystems used on the robot. One of the big items we have gotten working is incorporating the new PathPlanner 2.0 with our swerve for future autonomous (did have to make some minor changes to the libraries). The PID Controllers in this code is done entirely on the roboRIO for practice with plans to move some to the SparkMAX controllers.

Some of our 2022 code I’m sure may borrow almost directly from this.

Thank you for adding this thread. I was wondering how best to upload ours.
Here is 6762’s code.
Our 2020-2021 code is written in Python. It is relatively simple but worked well for us. The servo is for our BB8 head
In our post-season tournaments, we added the limelight. Which you can see here
Last year we began using onshape, and it is the first year we actually CADDed our bot. We did not include the container for the power cells, but it was literally just a Lexan box angled in to create a passive indexer.

We are transitioning to Java and used the Romi to learn this. Our Romi code uses the command framework and pathweaver to follow a trajectory. We also created a class to test waypoints in real-time using the simulator.

Here is a CADD of our Romi with the Intake for Alliance Antics.
